abstract = {Citizen science represents an immersive approach to engaging the public in scientific endeavors. Although not a new phenomenon, the rise of the Internet and technological innovations have accelerated the rate at which citizen science projects have spread around the world and vastly increased the amount of data collected by volunteers. This chapter provides an overview of citizen science, as well as some variants. It explores both its benefits and challenges. The myriad of ways libraries and librarians can support citizen science are also discussed, and two case studies outline the experiences and insights of librarians who have harnessed the power of citizen science to increase the public’s understanding of the scientific process, while also making the world a better place.}
